Consider the following code, especially the middle commented line:

``` C
int main() {
    if (true) {
        //this line is indented with two tabs
    }
}
```

If the cursor is placed between the two tabs on line 3, pressing Home sends the cursor to the beginning of the text (right before `//this ...`), which is in fact _after_ the original position. This is rather counter-intuitive, as one would expect the Home button to send the cursor left instead of right.

Atom 0.146.0 on Windows 7 64-bit.
